public class ObjectCache<T extends Object>
extends java.lang.Object

With this class you can easily cache OSM objects you received from the API, including their history. The properties of each OSM object are determined by reading their “id” and “version” XML attribute. For each ID the single versions are cached. The most current version of an object is specially marked, so you have to use the cacheCurrent() method instead of cacheVersion() to cache it. (Or you pass the whole history using cacheHistory().)
